<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="987" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d987">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3280.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Consul at
                                    Frontera</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-19T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You may circulate the President’s proclamation, March 2, as you propose,
                            but its language should be in nowise altered and great discretion should
                            be used.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>